Peru Stocks: Atacocha, Candente, El Brocal, Maple Advance

-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 
2011-08-12T20:45:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-12/peru-stocks-atacocha-candente-el-brocal-maple-advance.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:15 p.m. New York time.  The Lima General Index rose 1.3 percent to 19,937.43. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index gained 1.2 percent to 2,535.73.  Mining and energy stocks advanced as copper and crude oil
prices rose after higher U.S. retail sales tempered concern
about a slowdown in the global economy.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , the Canadian mining
exploration company with operations in Peru, climbed the most in
a month, rising 7 percent to $1.22. Cia. Minera Atacocha SA
(ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based silver and zinc mining company,
rose 3 percent to 1.02 soles, a one-week high. Sociedad Minera
El Brocal SAA (BROCALC1 PE), a zinc and lead producer, gained
2.1 percent to 46.98 soles.  Maple Energy Plc. (MPLE)  , the oil
and natural gas producer with operations in Peru, advanced 2.9
percent to a one-week high of $1.08.  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN PE), the countryâ€™s
biggest precious-metals miner, fell the most in a week as gold
prices declined. The Lima-based company slid 1.2 percent to
$41.75.  To contact the reporter on this story:
